        "part_type": "Hadith",
        "path": "/books/al-kafi:6:6:62:2",
        "text": [
          " سَأَلْتُ أَبَا الْحَسَنِ ( عليه السلام ) عَنْ لُحُومِ الْجَوَامِيسِ وَ أَلْبَانِهَا فَقَالَ لَا بَأْسَ بِهِمَا ."
        ],
        "translations": {
          "en.hubeali": [
            "Muhammad Bin Yahya, from Muhammad Bin Al Husay, from Safwan, from Abdullah Bin Jundab who said, ",
            "‘I asked Abu Al-Hassan<sup>asws</sup> about the Buffalo meats and their milks. So he<sup>asws</sup> said: ‘There is no problem with these’."
          ],
          "en.sarwar": [
            "2. Muhammad ibn Yahya has narrated from Muhammad ibn abu al-Hassan from Safwan from ‘Abd Allah ibn Jundab who has said the following: “I once asked abu al-Hassan, ‘Alayhi al-Salam, about the meat of a buffalos and its milk. He (the Imam) said, ‘It is not unlawful to use such items for food.’” "
          ]
